The IGV screenshots show views of RNA-seq, ATAC-seq, non-coding OCRs, gene annotation, and Hi-C data.
The RNA-seq tracks (red) show gene expression in this region, with visible peaks corresponding to actively transcribing genes.
The ATAC-seq tracks (blue) show regions of open chromatin, meaning accessible DNA.
The non-coding OCR tracks show open chromatin regions that do not overlap exons, showing potential regulatory elements, such as enhancers.
The gene annotation track (green) identifies the location and structure of genes within this region.
The Hi-C data (purple arcs) show chromatin looping interactions, showing physical contact between distant genomic regions.
Altogether, these regions show that non-coding open chromatin regions may regulate gene expression through long-range chromatin interactions.
